2002-**Trial-prior maintenance.** The `TRIAL_DERIVED_EFFECT_PRIORS` table is hard-coded in the demo. Production maintains this registry as a separate config artifact, reviewed quarterly by a disease-specific clinical advisor, with explicit citations to the source trials and the methodology used to derive the effect-size point estimates and credible intervals. New trial publications, meta-analyses, and post-marketing studies trigger a controlled prior update with explicit clinical sign-off. Without this, the counterfactual layer ages out of clinical alignment within eighteen to twenty-four months.
